Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 628
An Act Regarding Eligibility to Apply for a Department of
Education Diploma
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 20, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Education and Cultural Affairs pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to
Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative BRENNAN of Portland.
Cosponsored by Senator RAFFERTY of York and
Representatives: BRIDGEO of Augusta, CLOUTIER of Lewiston, DHALAC of South
Portland, DODGE of Belfast, MURPHY of Scarborough, RANA of Bangor, STOVER of
Boothbay, Senator: PIERCE of Cumberland.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA ยง257-A, sub-ยง1-C is enacted to read:
3 1-C. Exception for significant interruption to student's education conditions. A
4 student is eligible to apply for a Department of Education diploma if that student is a 4th
5 year secondary school student and is unable to satisfy the requirements for a diploma from
6 a school administrative unit because of a significant interruption to the student's education
7 conditions as approved by the commissioner during the student's secondary school
8 education history.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill provides that a student is eligible to apply for a Department of Education
1111 diploma if that student is a 4th year secondary school student and is unable to satisfy the
1122 requirements for a diploma from a school administrative unit because of a significant
1133 interruption to the student's education conditions as approved by the Commissioner of
1144 Education during the student's secondary school education history.
